# Third-party licenses

Bevy Common Systems' compiled artifacts (chiefly the WebAssembly web showcase)
statically link the Rust crates listed below. Their licenses require the license
text to travel with the distribution, so this file ships alongside those builds.

This file is GENERATED by `cargo-about` from `about.toml` + `about.hbs` - do not
edit by hand. It is produced fresh at release time (and locally via
`scripts/gen-licenses.sh`), so it always matches the dependency graph it ships
with. bcs itself is MIT-licensed; see the top-level `LICENSE`.

